==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gordius
<hw>Gor"di*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Gordian</er>, 1.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of long,
slender, nematoid worms, parasitic in insects until near maturity, when
they leave the insect, and live in water, in which they deposit their
eggs; -- called also <altname>hair eel</altname>,
<altname>hairworm</altname>, and <altname>hair snake</altname>, from the
absurd, but common and widely diffused, notion that they are
metamorphosed horsehairs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gore</ent>⟦br⟧
